<h4>Solutions</h4>
<ol>
<li>\( f(x) = \begin{cases} -x & \text{if } x \le 0 \\ x & \text{if } x \ge 0 \end{cases} \)</li>
<li>This gives us that the distance between $3x$ and $21$ is $102$. This means that $3x = 21 \pm 102$. Therefore, this gives $x = 7 \pm 34$ when dividing by $3$ and therefore $x = 41$ and $x = -27$. In terms of solving absolute value inequalities, we express $|f(x)|<a$ as $-a < f(x) < a$ and $|f(x)| > a$ as $f(x) < -a$ or $f(x) > a$. Then, we remove the function applied on $x$ by applying the inverse to all portions of the inequality, and we have a domain of $x$ for which the inequality is true.</li>
<li>This gives us the second case, so we express it as ($x+2 < -5$ or $x+2 > 5$). Subtracting 2 from all sides, we get ($x \le -7$ or $x > 3$). Therefore, $3 - 7 = -4$.</li>
</ol>
