<h3>Multiplication</h3>
<p>To multiply two terms together, $ax^n$ and $bx^m$, the result would be $(a*b)x^{n+m}$. If we were to take $3x^5$ and $2x^3$ as an example, the result would be $(3*2)x^{5+3} = 6x^8$. We can use this to multiply expressions together. To multiply two expressions together, we multiply every term in one parenthesis with every term in the other parenthesis, and then add them together.</p>


