<h2 id="polynomial-long-division">Polynomial Long Division</h2>

<p>We can follow a process containing a couple of steps:</p>

<p>1. Arrange the polynomials from highest degree to least degree</p>
<p>2. Divide the leading terms to get the first term of your quotient</p>
<p>3. Multiply the entire divisor by the term achieved in part 2 and subtract it like long division</p>
<p>4. Repeat steps 2 and 3 until the degree of the remaining polynomial is less than that of the divisor</p>
<p>5. Combine the quotient with the remainder</p>

