<h4 id="vietas-formula">Vieta's Formula</h4>

<p>Many problems deal with finding the roots of a polynomial, and that's where Vieta's Formula comes into play. Vieta's formula allows us to find the sum and product of all of the roots of the polynomial using the ratios between certain coefficients.</p>

<p>Given the polynomial $P(x) = a_n x^n + a_{n-1} x^{n-1} + ... + a_2 x^2 + a_1 x + a_0$, and roots $r_{1}, r_{2}, … , r_{n}$, we have that</p>

<p>$r_{1} + r_{2} + … r_{n} = \frac{-a_{n-1}}{a_{n}}$</p>
<p>$r_{1}r_{2} + r_{2}r_{3} + … + r_{n-1}r_{n} = \frac{a_{n-2}}{a_{n}}$</p>
<p>$r_{1}r_{2}r_{3}...r_{n} = (-1)^n *(\frac{a_{0}}{a_{n}})$</p>

</div>
